{"hash":"31d5b4bf073d71c4984737c85f9203058fd77262","data":{"markdownPage":{"id":"4fe3023f9083c2e61647f2b035427b32","title":"Installation","description":"Installation instructions","path":"/docs/installation/","timeToRead":1,"content":"<h1 id=\"installation\"><a href=\"#installation\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Installation</h1>\n<p><em><strong>Note:</strong> for now there's only a demo project with fixture data as NumberNine is still in development. This will be improved.</em></p>\n<h2 id=\"docker-recommended\"><a href=\"#docker-recommended\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Docker (recommended)</h2>\n<p>You don't need to be familiar with Docker. Everything is taken care of for you.\nJust <a href=\"https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">download and install it</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"create-the-project\"><a href=\"#create-the-project\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Create the project</h3>\n<p>To create a new project, simply replace <code>my_project</code> by the name of your project and run:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">docker run --rm -it -u <span class=\"token string\">'1000:1000'</span> -v <span class=\"token environment constant\">$PWD</span>:/app numberninecms/php:7.4-fpm-dev <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">composer</span> create-project --ignore-platform-reqs --no-scripts <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n    numberninecms/demo:dev-develop my_project</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"build-containers-and-install\"><a href=\"#build-containers-and-install\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Build containers and install</h3>\n<p>Go to your new project root and run:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">make</span> docker-install</code></pre>\n<p>Done. Now visit <a href=\"https://localhost/\" target=\"_blank\">https://localhost/</a>.</p>\n<p>If you want another domain or port, run:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token assign-left variable\">SERVER_NAME</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>mydomain.wip <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">NGINX_PORT</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token number\">8080</span> docker-compose up</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"windows--linux--wsl-installation\"><a href=\"#windows--linux--wsl-installation\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Windows / Linux / WSL installation</h2>\n<p><strong>Requirements to install NumberNine:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.mysql.com/downloads/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">MySQL 8.0</a> or above</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://redis.io/download\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Redis</a> and <code>redis</code> PHP extension (<a href=\"https://pecl.php.net/package/redis\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Windows version</a>)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://getcomposer.org/download/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Composer 2</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://symfony.com/download\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Symfony executable</a></li>\n<li><code>make</code> (<a href=\"http://gnuwin32.sourceforge.net/packages/make.htm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Windows version</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"create-the-project-1\"><a href=\"#create-the-project-1\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Create the project</h3>\n<p>To create a new project with NumberNine, simply run:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">composer</span> create-project numberninecms/demo:dev-develop my_project</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"launch-installation\"><a href=\"#launch-installation\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Launch installation</h3>\n<p>Go to your new project root and run:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">make</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span></code></pre>\n<p>An installation wizard will ask you details of your database and create everything for you.</p>\n<h3 id=\"run-the-server\"><a href=\"#run-the-server\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Run the server</h3>\n<p>Now launch the local server and visit your website.</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">make</span> serve</code></pre>\n<p>You're done. Visit <a href=\"https://localhost:8080/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://localhost:8080/</a> or the given URL if different.</p>\n<h2 id=\"quick-start\"><a href=\"#quick-start\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Quick start</h2>\n<p>Either login by clicking the top right \"Login/Register\" link, or by accessing <code>/admin/</code>.</p>\n<p>Demo admin login: <strong>admin</strong><br/>\nDemo admin password: <strong>password</strong></p>\n","sidebar":"docs","next":"","prev":"/docs/screenshots/","headings":[{"depth":1,"value":"Installation","anchor":"#installation"},{"depth":2,"value":"Docker (recommended)","anchor":"#docker-recommended"},{"depth":3,"value":"Create the project","anchor":"#create-the-project"},{"depth":3,"value":"Build containers and install","anchor":"#build-containers-and-install"},{"depth":2,"value":"Windows / Linux / WSL installation","anchor":"#windows--linux--wsl-installation"},{"depth":3,"value":"Create the project","anchor":"#create-the-project-1"},{"depth":3,"value":"Launch installation","anchor":"#launch-installation"},{"depth":3,"value":"Run the server","anchor":"#run-the-server"},{"depth":2,"value":"Quick start","anchor":"#quick-start"}]},"allMarkdownPage":{"edges":[{"node":{"path":"/docs/screenshots/","title":"Screenshots"}},{"node":{"path":"/docs/installation/","title":"Installation"}},{"node":{"path":"/docs/","title":"Introduction"}}]}},"context":{}}